    "As discussed, the matter of antiquities trade encompasses a variety of perspectives, methodologies, data sources, and network models from diverse fields of study.",
    "In this multidisciplinary realm, numerous approaches and viewpoints have been employed to analyse this intricate phenomenon.",
    "Given the demonstrated benefits of applying SNA in this field, it is only logical to explore graph theory as a whole and expand the research focus to include graph databases and KGs, as highlighted by Dörpinghaus et al. (2022).",
    "Rapid progress in cultural heritage KGs (Pellegrino, Scarano & Spagnuolo 2022) contrasts with limited development in illicit trafficking of antiquities.",
    "Brennan and Tsirogiannis (2022) work on an interactive KG using the forensic data from Christos Tsirogiannis is one first example."
